pokedexEntries.red: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.
pokedexEntries.blue: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Very powerful in spite of its small size. Its mastery of many types of martial arts makes it very tough.
pokedexEntries.gold: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.
pokedexEntries.silver: It loves to work out and build its muscles. It is never satisfied, even if it trains hard all day long.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It trains by lifting rocks in the mountains. It can even pick up a Graveler with ease.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Machop's muscles are special - they never get sore no matter how much they are used in exercise. This Pokémon has sufficient power to hurl a hundred adult humans.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Machop exercises by hefting around a Graveler as if it were a barbell. There are some Machop that travel the world in a quest to master all kinds of martial arts.
pokedexEntries.emerald: It continually undertakes strenuous training to master all forms of martial arts. Its strength lets it easily hoist a sumo wrestler onto its shoulders.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.
pokedexEntries.diamond: It hefts a Graveler repeatedly to strengthen its entire body. It uses every type of martial arts.
pokedexEntries.pearl: Its muscles never cramp however much it trains. It lives in the mountains away from humans.
pokedexEntries.platinum: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: It loves to work out and build its muscles. It is never satisfied, even if it trains hard all day long.
pokedexEntries.black: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.
pokedexEntries.white: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.
pokedexEntries.black2: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.
pokedexEntries.white2: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.
pokedexEntries.x: It hefts a Graveler repeatedly to strengthen its entire body. It uses every type of martial arts.
pokedexEntries.y: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Machop's muscles are special—they never get sore no matter how much they are used in exercise. This Pokémon has sufficient power to hurl a hundred adult humans.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Machop exercises by hefting around a Graveler as if it were a barbell. There are some Machop that travel the world in a quest to master all kinds of martial arts.
pokedexEntries.sun: It loves working out. As it gazes at its muscles, which continue to swell day by day, it becomes more and more dedicated to its training.
pokedexEntries.moon: With its superhuman strength, it's able to throw a hundred people all at the same time. Its strength comes from lifting Graveler every day.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: Once this Pokémon has gained enough confidence and muscle from training with its friends, it challenges Makuhita to a battle.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: It likes food that’s highly nutritious because its instincts drive it to build muscle efficiently.
